thread.title_full: Bush to campaign in North Las Vegas, Reno on Wednesday | Las Vegas Review-Journal

author: Ben Botkin
title: Bush to campaign in North Las Vegas, Reno on Wednesday
text:
Republican presidential candidate Jeb Bush will visit Nevada on Wednesday, making stops in Reno and North Las Vegas.
Bush will unveil his western land and resource management plan at a policy roundtable event in Reno on Wednesday. He'll go from there to a policy forum in North Las Vegas called "The LIBRE Forum: Unlimited Opportunities in a Free Society."
The forum in North Las Vegas starts at 6 p.m. Wednesday at the College of Southern Nevada Cheyenne Campus, Horn Theatre, 3200 E. Cheyenne Ave., North Las Vegas.
It's hosted by The LIBRE Initiative and is aimed at covering issues impacting the Hispanic community, including the economy, education, immigration and healthcare. Doors open at 5 p.m.
The organization is a non-partisan group with the goal of educating Hispanics about issues, including limited government and free enterprise.
The Reno event is not open to the general public. The North Las Vegas event is open to the public. To RSVP for the North Las Vegas event, visit http://thelibreforum.com/bush/ .
Contact Ben Botkin at bbotkin@reviewjournal.com or 702-387-2904. Find him on Twitter: @BenBotkin1
